column1: (1)In the column of enterovirus type, "Others" refers to enteroviruses of unidentified virus type;
(2)The criteria for "Frequently, Occasionally and Hardly": "Frequently" means not less than 3 times each week. "Occasionally" means 1 to 2 times per week. "Hardly" means 0 times per week;

(3)The criteria for"Regularly", Occasionally irregular and Irregularly":"Regularly" is defined as being able to eat every meal on time. "Occasionally irregular" is defined as not being able to eat on time 1-2 times a week. "Irregularly" is defined as not being able to eat on time or not eating more than 2 times a week.
